Knowledge & Proposal Intelligence Copilot
Architecture of the Unified Agent

The unified agent should orchestrate these 3 internal specialized agents:

Internal Agent	Purpose	Primary Users
Client Account Intelligence Agent	Provides a 360° view of client accounts, engagements, and communications	Account Managers, Engagement Managers, Delivery Leads
Proposal & Knowledge Reuse Agent	Finds relevant proposals, case studies, reusable content, and client deliverables	Sales, Presales, Bid Managers, Consultants
Methodology & Delivery Excellence Agent	Guides teams on delivery methodologies, frameworks, SOPs, and best practices	Consultants, Project Managers, Delivery Teams

The user interacts with ONE agent only.

Internally, the agent decides which capability to use based on the user's request.

Why These 3 Agents?

These three capabilities represent the core knowledge needs across consulting and professional services:

Client intelligence – Understanding client history, ongoing engagements, stakeholders, and previous work.
Knowledge reuse – Accelerating proposal creation by leveraging existing assets, case studies, and reusable content.
Delivery guidance – Ensuring consistent execution using approved methodologies, templates, and best practices.

Together, they reduce time spent searching for information, improve consistency across projects, and increase the reuse of organizational knowledge while relying solely on Microsoft 365 content.

Unified Agent Responsibilities

The unified agent should:

1. Client Account Intelligence
Summarize client accounts and active engagements.
Retrieve previous project deliverables, presentations, and meeting notes.
Identify key stakeholders and recent client interactions.
Highlight commitments, milestones, and ongoing workstreams.
Surface similar engagements completed for the same client.
2. Proposal & Knowledge Reuse
Find relevant proposals, RFP responses, and case studies.
Recommend reusable content for proposals and presentations.
Retrieve capability decks, solution descriptions, and supporting collateral.
Identify similar engagements that can strengthen new proposals.
Summarize previous winning approaches and client-specific assets.
3. Methodology & Delivery Excellence
Recommend appropriate delivery methodologies and frameworks.
Retrieve SOPs, governance documents, and quality checklists.
Suggest project templates, deliverables, and documentation standards.
Explain internal best practices for research, analytics, and consulting engagements.
Surface lessons learned and reusable delivery assets from previous projects.
